# Markdown Skill

> Documentation patterns, README structure, and formatting.

---

## Basic Syntax

### Headers
```markdown
# H1 - Document Title
## H2 - Main Section
### H3 - Subsection
#### H4 - Sub-subsection
```

### Text Formatting
```markdown
**bold** or __bold__
*italic* or _italic_
***bold italic***
~~strikethrough~~
`inline code`
```

### Links & Images
```markdown
[Link text](https://example.com)
[Link with title](https://example.com "Title")
[Reference link][ref-id]

![Alt text](image.png)
![Alt text](image.png "Title")

[ref-id]: https://example.com
```

### Lists
```markdown
- Unordered item
- Another item
  - Nested item
  - Another nested

1. Ordered item
2. Another item
   1. Nested ordered
   2. Another nested

- [ ] Task item
- [x] Completed task
```

